minister Paul Hellyer

00:00:44.120 --> 00:00:46.150 align:middle line:84%
has been keeping an
eye on the money mafia

00:00:46.150 --> 00:00:48.140 align:middle line:90%
throughout his life and career.

00:00:48.140 --> 00:00:49.810 align:middle line:84%
I caught up with
him in Los Angeles

00:00:49.810 --> 00:00:52.540 align:middle line:84%
to learn just how deep
the corruption goes

00:00:52.540 --> 00:00:55.670 align:middle line:84%
and what's required of us
to take back our system.

00:00:55.670 --> 00:00:58.610 align:middle line:84%
Paul, we're back, and we could
not end the conversation.

00:00:58.610 --> 00:01:01.110 align:middle line:84%
You brought up a couple juicy
pearls in your background

00:01:01.110 --> 00:01:04.069 align:middle line:84%
in economics and your
book, "The Money Mafia."

00:01:04.069 --> 00:01:06.410 align:middle line:84%
I really wanted to have
this conversation with you

00:01:06.410 --> 00:01:09.380 align:middle line:84%
because we are a slave
species, but not in the way

00:01:09.380 --> 00:01:11.370 align:middle line:90%
that some of the people mean.

00:01:11.370 --> 00:01:14.900 align:middle line:84%
We're a slave species to a
horrid economic system that has

00:01:14.900 --> 00:01:17.309 align:middle line:90%
been artificially constructed.

00:01:17.309 --> 00:01:18.850 align:middle line:84%
>>PAUL HELLYER:
We're slaves to debt.

00:01:18.850 --> 00:01:20.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We're slaves to debt.

00:01:20.440 --> 00:01:22.210 align:middle line:90%
Now I'm going to start it out.

00:01:22.210 --> 00:01:25.120 align:middle line:84%
And in your book,
you make this comment

00:01:25.120 --> 00:01:26.790 align:middle line:84%
at the beginning of
one of the chapters,

00:01:26.790 --> 00:01:29.240 align:middle line:84%
that you always kept
an eye on the mafia

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:30.310 align:middle line:90%
throughout your career.

00:01:30.310 --> 00:01:32.780 align:middle line:84%
You kind of needed to
know what they were up to.

00:01:32.780 --> 00:01:34.690 align:middle line:84%
Let's start the
conversation there.

00:01:34.690 --> 00:01:35.845 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:01:35.845 --> 00:01:36.645 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Why?

00:01:36.645 --> 00:01:40.050 align:middle line:84%
Because they have a way of
compromising politicians.

00:01:40.050 --> 00:01:40.890 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:01:40.890 --> 00:01:47.890 align:middle line:10%
>>HELLYER: They will contribute
to your campaign funds,

00:01:47.890 --> 00:01:50.170 align:middle line:10%
just normally.

00:01:50.170 --> 00:01:53.630 align:middle line:84%
And unless you know who
they are and what they are,

00:01:53.630 --> 00:01:56.040 align:middle line:90%
you won't even know about it.

00:01:56.040 --> 00:01:59.690 align:middle line:84%
And maybe eventually, years
later, you might find out.

00:01:59.690 --> 00:02:03.466 align:middle line:84%
Or there might be some
request, something like that.

00:02:03.466 --> 00:02:06.290 align:middle line:84%
And I've had personal
experience when

00:02:06.290 --> 00:02:13.060 align:middle line:84%
I was dabbling with a little
private political party at one

00:02:13.060 --> 00:02:13.860 align:middle line:90%
time.

00:02:13.860 --> 00:02:16.940 align:middle line:90%
I got a check for $5,000.

00:02:16.940 --> 00:02:20.410 align:middle line:84%
And it came with a
letter that said,

00:02:20.410 --> 00:02:23.076 align:middle line:84%
there's more where
this came from.

00:02:23.076 --> 00:02:26.200 align:middle line:84%
Being a little bit suspicious,
I thought to myself,

00:02:26.200 --> 00:02:28.520 align:middle line:90%
I wonder what that's all about.

00:02:28.520 --> 00:02:29.980 align:middle line:84%
So I got in touch
with the editor

00:02:29.980 --> 00:02:32.290 align:middle line:84%
of our major paper,
the "Toronto Star,"

00:02:32.290 --> 00:02:36.480 align:middle line:84%
and asked if he could
give me any leads.

00:02:36.480 --> 00:02:38.710 align:middle line:84%
About two weeks
later, he wrote back

00:02:38.710 --> 00:02:44.260 align:middle line:84%
and he said, yes, that's the
lawyer for the number one mafia

00:02:44.260 --> 00:02:47.140 align:middle line:90%
guy in the Hamilton area.

00:02:47.140 --> 00:02:48.144 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:02:48.144 --> 00:02:50.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you started
learning about shadow

00:02:50.060 --> 00:02:51.040 align:middle line:90%
operations early on.

00:02:51.040 --> 00:02:51.840 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Right.

00:02:51.840 --> 00:02:54.630 align:middle line:84%
So the check went
back, despite the fact

00:02:54.630 --> 00:02:59.505 align:middle line:84%
that it would have been
very useful at the time.

00:02:59.505 --> 00:03:02.690 align:middle line:84%
No, it's just something
to keep track of.

00:03:02.690 --> 00:03:03.490 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:03:03.490 --> 00:03:04.500 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: So I--

00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:05.875 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So it
was the beginning

00:03:05.875 --> 00:03:08.660 align:middle line:84%
of looking at shadow
effects of money.

00:03:08.660 --> 00:03:11.020 align:middle line:84%
And I have a question, and I
don't know if it's relevant

00:03:11.020 --> 00:03:11.910 align:middle line:90%
or not.

00:03:11.910 --> 00:03:15.040 align:middle line:84%
Having looked at that and
watched how that works--

00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:18.690 align:middle line:84%
and we know, just mostly
through fictionalized accounts

00:03:18.690 --> 00:03:21.750 align:middle line:84%
and some news, how those
kinds of cartels work.

00:03:21.750 --> 00:03:24.130 align:middle line:84%
But let's now start
dovetailing that

00:03:24.130 --> 00:03:27.090 align:middle line:84%
into how the cartel at
large is working now,

00:03:27.090 --> 00:03:30.590 align:middle line:84%
and the similarities between the
mafia and the current cartels.

00:03:30.590 --> 00:03:32.980 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: Well, most
people, first of all,

00:03:32.980 --> 00:03:35.470 align:middle line:90%
don't know what money is.

00:03:35.470 --> 00:03:37.990 align:middle line:90%
And so let's start there.

00:03:37.990 --> 00:03:39.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:03:39.080 --> 00:03:43.055 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: The change you have
in your pocket or in your purse

00:03:43.055 --> 00:03:45.530 align:middle line:90%
is less than 1%.

00:03:45.530 --> 00:03:48.360 align:middle line:90%
Just change.

00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:53.410 align:middle line:84%
The bills you carry in your
pocketbook or purse and so on,

00:03:53.410 --> 00:03:59.170 align:middle line:84%
or have stashed around, are,
depending on circumstances,

00:03:59.170 --> 00:04:01.820 align:middle line:90%
maybe 3% of money.

00:04:01.820 --> 00:04:05.780 align:middle line:90%
All the rest are bank deposits.

00:04:05.780 --> 00:04:07.290 align:middle line:90%
It is virtual money.

00:04:07.290 --> 00:04:08.980 align:middle line:90%
It is not real money.

00:04:08.980 --> 00:04:11.430 align:middle line:84%
It is not legal tender,
although it is used

00:04:11.430 --> 00:04:14.740 align:middle line:90%
as if it were legal tender.

00:04:14.740 --> 00:04:23.030 align:middle line:84%
It is a global fraud, F-R-A-U-D.
And it's a Ponzi scheme worse

00:04:23.030 --> 00:04:29.940 align:middle line:84%
than Bernie Madoff's in the
sense that it has affected tens

00:04:29.940 --> 00:04:32.330 align:middle line:84%
of thousands of people
all over the world,

00:04:32.330 --> 00:04:35.450 align:middle line:84%
and wrecked their lives, and
wrecked their businesses.

00:04:35.450 --> 00:04:41.930 align:middle line:84%
And it is because
all of that money

00:04:41.930 --> 00:04:49.150 align:middle line:84%
is created as debt, which has
to be repaid with interest.

00:04:49.150 --> 00:04:52.280 align:middle line:84%
But nobody creates
any money with which

00:04:52.280 --> 00:04:55.990 align:middle line:84%
to repay either
principal or interest.

00:04:55.990 --> 00:04:58.600 align:middle line:84%
So it doesn't take you long
to figure out what to do.

00:04:58.600 --> 00:05:02.950 align:middle line:84%
You have to borrow more in order
to pay the interest on what

00:05:02.950 --> 00:05:05.120 align:middle line:90%
you already know.

00:05:05.120 --> 00:05:09.935 align:middle line:84%
Now, the sort of relationship
to the mafia that I

00:05:09.935 --> 00:05:14.450 align:middle line:84%
have in my book is that we
have had an investigation

00:05:14.450 --> 00:05:19.200 align:middle line:84%
in our city of
Montreal in Canada.

00:05:19.200 --> 00:05:24.970 align:middle line:84%
And it was brought into the
evidence-- the allegation,

00:05:24.970 --> 00:05:29.070 align:middle line:84%
at least-- that the mafia had
been creaming off 2% or 2.5%

00:05:29.070 --> 00:05:34.670 align:middle line:84%
of all the contracts for public
works in the city for years.

00:05:34.670 --> 00:05:42.120 align:middle line:84%
The bankers only need $0.05
to create $1 in money that

00:05:42.120 --> 00:05:44.000 align:middle line:90%
has to be repaid with interest.

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:46.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: They're skimming 95%.

00:05:46.520 --> 00:05:50.125 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: 95% off
the top of every loan

00:05:50.125 --> 00:05:51.770 align:middle line:90%
that people take out.

00:05:51.770 --> 00:05:56.760 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's a mortgage,
or a loan for a car,

00:05:56.760 --> 00:06:00.800 align:middle line:84%
or to start a business, or to
expand a business, or whatever,

00:06:00.800 --> 00:06:03.710 align:middle line:90%
95% off the top.

00:06:03.710 --> 00:06:13.840 align:middle line:84%
So that is why you have
these absolutely enormous

00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:22.400 align:middle line:84%
wealthy people, where now 80
families own more than 50%

00:06:22.400 --> 00:06:25.930 align:middle line:84%
of the whole wealth
of the world.

00:06:25.930 --> 00:06:28.130 align:middle line:84%
And it's getting
worse all the time.

00:06:28.130 --> 00:06:30.855 align:middle line:84%
A year ago, I think
it was 88 families.

00:06:30.855 --> 00:06:32.105 align:middle line:90%
This is part of globalization.

00:06:32.105 --> 00:06:33.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Becoming
more concentrated, yes.

00:06:33.290 --> 00:06:34.690 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: Yeah, part
of globalization.

00:06:34.690 --> 00:06:34.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:06:34.970 --> 00:06:37.053 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: But it is
basically the banking system,

00:06:37.053 --> 00:06:41.400 align:middle line:84%
because they're buying up
assets all over the world

00:06:41.400 --> 00:06:42.650 align:middle line:90%
for $0.05 on the dollar.

00:06:42.650 --> 00:06:43.450 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:06:43.450 --> 00:06:44.866 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: And if
you can do that,

00:06:44.866 --> 00:06:48.910 align:middle line:84%
you can become immensely
wealthy in no time flat.

00:06:48.910 --> 00:06:49.840 align:middle line:90%
And that's exactly--

00:06:49.840 --> 00:06:51.256 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
and it's something

00:06:51.256 --> 00:06:52.445 align:middle line:90%
they gifted themselves.

00:06:52.445 --> 00:06:53.570 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Well, of course.

00:06:53.570 --> 00:06:59.250 align:middle line:84%
But politicians, kings,
queens, princes, presidents,

00:06:59.250 --> 00:07:03.880 align:middle line:90%
and others, have consented.

00:07:03.880 --> 00:07:07.960 align:middle line:84%
Because the difference between
Bernie Madoff and the bankers

00:07:07.960 --> 00:07:13.580 align:middle line:84%
is that the banks'
stealing is legal.

00:07:13.580 --> 00:07:14.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:07:14.950 --> 00:07:17.880 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: But there is
legislation that allows

00:07:17.880 --> 00:07:21.440 align:middle line:90%
them to do what they're doing.

00:07:21.440 --> 00:07:27.000 align:middle line:84%
And so the problem is to
change the legislation

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:30.250 align:middle line:90%
and to have a fairer system.

00:07:30.250 --> 00:07:32.290 align:middle line:84%
And as of now, what
needs to be done,

00:07:32.290 --> 00:07:37.910 align:middle line:84%
of course, because the
world is drowning in debt--

00:07:37.910 --> 00:07:42.630 align:middle line:84%
the debt situation at the moment
is the worst it has ever been,

00:07:42.630 --> 00:07:45.150 align:middle line:84%
I think in the
history of the world.

00:07:45.150 --> 00:07:47.700 align:middle line:84%
And it's getting worse
instead of better.

00:07:47.700 --> 00:07:51.210 align:middle line:84%
So what has to be
done is the infusion

00:07:51.210 --> 00:07:54.150 align:middle line:84%
of-- some days I use
"significant amounts."

00:07:54.150 --> 00:07:57.020 align:middle line:84%
Other days I say
"massive amounts"

00:07:57.020 --> 00:08:07.070 align:middle line:84%
of government-created, debt-free
money to make the whole mix,

00:08:07.070 --> 00:08:18.660 align:middle line:84%
to change it, to add a
different kind of money which

00:08:18.660 --> 00:08:22.490 align:middle line:84%
will allow the system to work
without having to go back

00:08:22.490 --> 00:08:25.690 align:middle line:90%
to the bankers and borrow.

00:08:25.690 --> 00:08:30.540 align:middle line:84%
And the interesting thing is,
the people own the rights.

00:08:30.540 --> 00:08:33.305 align:middle line:90%
In Canada, we own them outright.

00:08:33.305 --> 00:08:35.189 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You own what outright?

00:08:35.189 --> 00:08:36.730 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: The right
to create money.

00:08:36.730 --> 00:08:37.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, OK.

00:08:37.630 --> 00:08:38.850 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: 100% of it.

00:08:38.850 --> 00:08:40.929 align:middle line:90%
I'm not suggesting 100%.

00:08:40.929 --> 00:08:44.690 align:middle line:84%
Actually, in my book and
one or two recent books,

00:08:44.690 --> 00:08:50.430 align:middle line:90%
I have promoted the idea of 34%.

00:08:50.430 --> 00:08:55.375 align:middle line:84%
And that would be enough,
A, to reduce the leverage--

00:08:55.375 --> 00:08:59.110 align:middle line:84%
and we haven't talked about
leverage, but maybe we should--

00:08:59.110 --> 00:09:05.980 align:middle line:84%
from 20 to 1, which is creaming
95% off the top, to 2 to 1,

00:09:05.980 --> 00:09:08.610 align:middle line:90%
which is having to put up 50%.

00:09:08.610 --> 00:09:10.510 align:middle line:90%
And it's still a good deal.

00:09:10.510 --> 00:09:16.820 align:middle line:84%
But the banking industry
can play a role, still,

00:09:16.820 --> 00:09:20.710 align:middle line:84%
providing a little
credit to new businesses

00:09:20.710 --> 00:09:23.100 align:middle line:90%
and this sort of thing.

00:09:23.100 --> 00:09:25.290 align:middle line:84%
And that's the reason
that we can leave them

00:09:25.290 --> 00:09:29.400 align:middle line:84%
with a little bit of
money-creation power, which

00:09:29.400 --> 00:09:35.550 align:middle line:84%
is positive, but not with this
system where they can just

00:09:35.550 --> 00:09:37.120 align:middle line:90%
take it all.

00:09:37.120 --> 00:09:39.645 align:middle line:84%
And now they have a
monopoly in creating money.

00:09:39.645 --> 00:09:41.635 align:middle line:90%
And the monopoly must end.

00:09:41.635 --> 00:09:43.670 align:middle line:90%
It must end right away.

00:09:43.670 --> 00:09:46.840 align:middle line:84%
And governments have to
start creating enough money

00:09:46.840 --> 00:09:51.090 align:middle line:84%
to balance their books,
to balance their budgets,

00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:54.660 align:middle line:84%
and to meet the real
needs of the people

00:09:54.660 --> 00:09:56.740 align:middle line:90%
at reasonable tax rates.

00:09:56.740 --> 00:09:58.610 align:middle line:90%
That's what has to be done.

00:09:58.610 --> 00:10:02.000 align:middle line:84%
And you have a special
problem in the United States

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:05.680 align:middle line:84%
of major proportions,
unfortunately,

00:10:05.680 --> 00:10:11.120 align:middle line:84%
that you have this monster, the
Federal Reserve system, around.

00:10:11.120 --> 00:10:12.250 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:10:12.250 --> 00:10:15.720 align:middle line:84%
Well, for anyone
to-- just because we

00:10:15.720 --> 00:10:17.150 align:middle line:90%
can't get into all of it.

00:10:17.150 --> 00:10:18.940 align:middle line:84%
But they can go to
"Creature from Jekyll

00:10:18.940 --> 00:10:20.330 align:middle line:90%
Island," for example, and--

00:10:20.330 --> 00:10:21.413 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Oh, absolutely.

00:10:21.413 --> 00:10:24.209 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, Griffin's
site, and get the book

00:10:24.209 --> 00:10:25.750 align:middle line:84%
and start educating
yourself on that.

00:10:25.750 --> 00:10:27.651 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Or "The Web of Debt."

00:10:27.651 --> 00:10:29.275 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: "Web of
Debt" by Ellen Brown.

00:10:29.275 --> 00:10:31.540 align:middle line:84%
And I've done some interviews
with her too, so there's--

00:10:31.540 --> 00:10:33.950 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: And you just have to
read the first hundred pages.

00:10:33.950 --> 00:10:34.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:10:34.750 --> 00:10:38.550 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: Including
how Morgan Bank

00:10:38.550 --> 00:10:41.480 align:middle line:84%
gained control of the
press so that they wouldn't

00:10:41.480 --> 00:10:43.260 align:middle line:90%
talk about these issues.

00:10:43.260 --> 00:10:44.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:10:44.060 --> 00:10:45.470 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Sending people out.

00:10:45.470 --> 00:10:47.020 align:middle line:84%
What are the most
important papers?

00:10:47.020 --> 00:10:48.270 align:middle line:90%
Well, here they are.

00:10:48.270 --> 00:10:51.560 align:middle line:84%
Get control of the 25 most
important papers in the United

00:10:51.560 --> 00:10:52.370 align:middle line:90%
States.

00:10:52.370 --> 00:10:55.690 align:middle line:84%
They will never mention
our creaming them.

00:10:55.690 --> 00:10:56.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:10:56.770 --> 00:10:58.311 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: Because
we won't let them.

00:10:58.311 --> 00:11:00.740 align:middle line:84%
It's the same kind of
secrecy that actually

00:11:00.740 --> 00:11:03.550 align:middle line:90%
applies in the UFO field.

00:11:03.550 --> 00:11:04.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:11:04.350 --> 00:11:07.390 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: So that
nothing gets in the paper,

00:11:07.390 --> 00:11:12.760 align:middle line:84%
because there is an
embargo on those issues.

00:11:12.760 --> 00:11:13.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:11:13.600 --> 00:11:16.200 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: And probably it
is done exactly the same way

00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:20.670 align:middle line:84%
as Morgan Bank did a
little over 100 years ago,

00:11:20.670 --> 00:11:22.710 align:middle line:90%
when the Fed was formed.

00:11:22.710 --> 00:11:23.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:11:23.510 --> 00:11:25.390 align:middle line:84%
OK, now we're going
to backtrack because I

00:11:25.390 --> 00:11:28.060 align:middle line:84%
want to get into
the anatomy of this

00:11:28.060 --> 00:11:31.720 align:middle line:84%
and how a lot of the trouble
we're in today began.

00:11:31.720 --> 00:11:37.350 align:middle line:84%
I want to go back into pre-World
War II, back through IG Farben,

00:11:37.350 --> 00:11:39.450 align:middle line:84%
Nazis, Bank of
International Settlements,

00:11:39.450 --> 00:11:44.670 align:middle line:84%
and do a little anatomy of
war equals debt equals profit.

00:11:44.670 --> 00:11:46.365 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Well, yeah.

00:11:46.365 --> 00:11:47.430 align:middle line:90%
Anything that--

00:11:47.430 --> 00:11:49.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because we have
wars going constantly.

00:11:49.860 --> 00:11:50.660 align:middle line:90%
It's for a reason.

00:11:50.660 --> 00:11:52.326 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: Where you
have any borrowing,

00:11:52.326 --> 00:11:56.950 align:middle line:84%
which you have to have in war,
then that's good for the banks

00:11:56.950 --> 00:12:00.130 align:middle line:84%
and bad for the people, because
they're left with the debt.

00:12:00.130 --> 00:12:05.840 align:middle line:84%
The people that make the
munitions make a lot of money.

00:12:05.840 --> 00:12:08.050 align:middle line:90%
The banks make a lot of money.

00:12:08.050 --> 00:12:10.590 align:middle line:84%
A lot of ordinary
people get killed.

00:12:10.590 --> 00:12:14.650 align:middle line:84%
Their families' lives
are disrupted, and so on.

00:12:14.650 --> 00:12:17.880 align:middle line:84%
And they are left
with the debt, which

00:12:17.880 --> 00:12:20.420 align:middle line:84%
they have to pay,
and not only repay

00:12:20.420 --> 00:12:22.570 align:middle line:90%
principal, but also interest.

00:12:22.570 --> 00:12:25.640 align:middle line:84%
Which they can't do, because
there's no money with which

00:12:25.640 --> 00:12:26.720 align:middle line:90%
to repay it.

00:12:26.720 --> 00:12:29.240 align:middle line:84%
So it just keeps getting
larger and larger and larger.

00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:30.920 align:middle line:84%
And you folks in
the United States

00:12:30.920 --> 00:12:33.830 align:middle line:84%
have this charade that
you have to go through

00:12:33.830 --> 00:12:36.500 align:middle line:84%
every once in a while to
increase the credit limit.

00:12:36.500 --> 00:12:37.970 align:middle line:90%
[REGINA SNORTING]

00:12:37.970 --> 00:12:40.840 align:middle line:84%
Whereas it would not
be necessary at all

00:12:40.840 --> 00:12:43.890 align:middle line:84%
if we had a system that
was the least bit sensible,

00:12:43.890 --> 00:12:48.310 align:middle line:84%
because the federal government
could create enough money

00:12:48.310 --> 00:12:51.330 align:middle line:90%
to balance its budget.

00:12:51.330 --> 00:12:53.740 align:middle line:84%
An important point
is that people

00:12:53.740 --> 00:12:56.530 align:middle line:84%
say you have to live
within your means.

00:12:56.530 --> 00:12:58.340 align:middle line:90%
Well, we, as individuals, do.

00:12:58.340 --> 00:13:00.260 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:13:00.260 --> 00:13:02.680 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: And state
governments do.

00:13:02.680 --> 00:13:04.980 align:middle line:90%
And municipalities have to.

00:13:04.980 --> 00:13:07.050 align:middle line:84%
But federal governments
don't because they

00:13:07.050 --> 00:13:10.670 align:middle line:90%
own the patent to create money.

00:13:10.670 --> 00:13:14.330 align:middle line:84%
And we have a proposal
in Canada that's

00:13:14.330 --> 00:13:23.630 align:middle line:84%
been talked about of creating
cash by instead of giving out

00:13:23.630 --> 00:13:30.300 align:middle line:84%
bonds to borrow money, that
they create share certificates

00:13:30.300 --> 00:13:34.210 align:middle line:84%
in the country, just
in nominal amounts

00:13:34.210 --> 00:13:36.280 align:middle line:90%
of so many billions of dollars.

00:13:36.280 --> 00:13:39.140 align:middle line:84%
Hand them to the
central bank in exchange

00:13:39.140 --> 00:13:41.370 align:middle line:84%
for cash, which
is then deposited

00:13:41.370 --> 00:13:44.260 align:middle line:90%
in the government's accounts.

00:13:44.260 --> 00:13:47.930 align:middle line:84%
And in Canada, we're suggesting
a certain amount, $150 billion

00:13:47.930 --> 00:13:51.872 align:middle line:84%
a year for seven years,
and split equally

00:13:51.872 --> 00:13:54.455 align:middle line:84%
between the federal government
and the provincial governments.

00:13:54.455 --> 00:13:56.380 align:middle line:84%
So we'd share it with
the municipalities.

00:13:56.380 --> 00:13:59.860 align:middle line:84%
And this would be
enough for everyone

00:13:59.860 --> 00:14:01.250 align:middle line:90%
to balance their books.

00:14:01.250 --> 00:14:02.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Sounds
totally rational.

00:14:02.740 --> 00:14:05.010 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: Absolutely
totally rational.

00:14:05.010 --> 00:14:09.010 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, the
economy would take off.

00:14:09.010 --> 00:14:12.160 align:middle line:84%
And the despair of the
present young generation,

00:14:12.160 --> 00:14:13.950 align:middle line:84%
who quote unquote
"are not going to

00:14:13.950 --> 00:14:16.460 align:middle line:84%
do as well as their parents"
because of the system--

00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:18.084 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're
left holding the bag.

00:14:18.084 --> 00:14:18.960 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Yeah.

00:14:18.960 --> 00:14:20.870 align:middle line:90%
They will have renewed hope.

00:14:20.870 --> 00:14:22.440 align:middle line:90%
So easy.

00:14:22.440 --> 00:14:25.250 align:middle line:84%
But the problem
is it's too easy,

00:14:25.250 --> 00:14:29.180 align:middle line:84%
and the other that money
mafia have too much power

00:14:29.180 --> 00:14:32.870 align:middle line:84%
and are willing to grease
the palms of people

00:14:32.870 --> 00:14:35.320 align:middle line:84%
that will support them
one way or another.

00:14:35.320 --> 00:14:38.070 align:middle line:90%
But something has to change.

00:14:38.070 --> 00:14:39.155 align:middle line:90%
Otherwise--

00:14:39.155 --> 00:14:43.400 align:middle line:84%
I've been reading
several papers recently,

00:14:43.400 --> 00:14:46.530 align:middle line:84%
who say there will probably
be another recession

00:14:46.530 --> 00:14:48.230 align:middle line:90%
within the next two years.

00:14:48.230 --> 00:14:51.450 align:middle line:84%
And then some people say,
maybe three or four years.

00:14:51.450 --> 00:14:53.900 align:middle line:84%
We don't need any
more recessions.

00:14:53.900 --> 00:14:55.685 align:middle line:84%
Heavenly days, I
forget how many there

00:14:55.685 --> 00:15:01.370 align:middle line:84%
have been in the last 100 years,
but 30, or something like that?

00:15:01.370 --> 00:15:04.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
theoretically they can't do

00:15:04.230 --> 00:15:06.170 align:middle line:90%
what they've done in the past.

00:15:06.170 --> 00:15:09.220 align:middle line:84%
So the quantitative easing,
people are kind of on to that.

00:15:09.220 --> 00:15:10.937 align:middle line:90%
There's no easing of anything.

00:15:10.937 --> 00:15:12.270 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing to ease it with.

00:15:12.270 --> 00:15:13.000 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Well--

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:14.208 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Under the current--

00:15:14.208 --> 00:15:18.320 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: Quantitative easing
was liquidity for the banks,

00:15:18.320 --> 00:15:19.200 align:middle line:90%
not for the people.

00:15:19.200 --> 00:15:20.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Not for the people.

00:15:20.140 --> 00:15:20.596 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: No.

00:15:20.596 --> 00:15:21.396 align:middle line:90%
That's--

00:15:21.396 --> 00:15:22.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, exactly.

00:15:22.580 --> 00:15:26.000 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: And they created
trillions of dollars

00:15:26.000 --> 00:15:28.240 align:middle line:84%
to bail out the banks
and some businesses,

00:15:28.240 --> 00:15:32.830 align:middle line:84%
who were the friends of the
shareholders of the Fed.

00:15:32.830 --> 00:15:35.000 align:middle line:84%
Because the Fed is a
private corporation.

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:35.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:15:35.890 --> 00:15:37.640 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: It's not
government-owned,

00:15:37.640 --> 00:15:40.100 align:middle line:90%
as we have in Canada.

00:15:40.100 --> 00:15:43.310 align:middle line:84%
And this was a big mistake made
a little over 100 years ago.

00:15:43.310 --> 00:15:44.783 align:middle line:90%
Everybody recognized it.

00:15:44.783 --> 00:15:47.355 align:middle line:84%
But in 100 years, Congress
hasn't done anything about it.

00:15:47.355 --> 00:15:48.155 align:middle line:90%
Long since--

00:15:48.155 --> 00:15:50.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Again, "Creature
from Jekyll Island," read it.

00:15:50.590 --> 00:15:51.390 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Yeah.

00:15:51.390 --> 00:15:55.820 align:middle line:84%
Long since time to
come to terms with it

00:15:55.820 --> 00:15:58.550 align:middle line:84%
and do something
so that you regain

00:15:58.550 --> 00:16:03.270 align:middle line:84%
control of the most important
economic tool in the toolbox.

00:16:03.270 --> 00:16:04.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:16:04.080 --> 00:16:06.230 align:middle line:84%
OK, so in your book,
as you were explaining

00:16:06.230 --> 00:16:08.707 align:middle line:84%
how, along the way,
how this played out,

00:16:08.707 --> 00:16:10.540 align:middle line:84%
one of the things I
found really interesting

00:16:10.540 --> 00:16:11.956 align:middle line:84%
was an area where
you were talking

00:16:11.956 --> 00:16:14.940 align:middle line:84%
about the Bank of
International Settlements--

00:16:14.940 --> 00:16:17.660 align:middle line:84%
this was pre-World
War II-- and the fact

00:16:17.660 --> 00:16:20.510 align:middle line:84%
that there were agreements
made between governments,

00:16:20.510 --> 00:16:25.730 align:middle line:84%
for example, that we were not
to bomb the IG Farben factories.

00:16:25.730 --> 00:16:28.280 align:middle line:84%
You had a lot of vehicles
being produced out of there.

00:16:28.280 --> 00:16:31.130 align:middle line:84%
Ford produced a lot of the
vehicles for the Nazi effort,

00:16:31.130 --> 00:16:32.750 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:16:32.750 --> 00:16:36.300 align:middle line:84%
And that it was agreed
upon because it was already

00:16:36.300 --> 00:16:39.400 align:middle line:84%
agreed that at the
conclusion of World War II,

00:16:39.400 --> 00:16:44.920 align:middle line:84%
if I'm understanding what
you said in there correctly,

00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:46.510 align:middle line:84%
the industry of
Germany was going

00:16:46.510 --> 00:16:49.440 align:middle line:84%
to be used to help
rebuild after the war,

00:16:49.440 --> 00:16:51.870 align:middle line:90%
so please spare those factories.

00:16:51.870 --> 00:16:55.870 align:middle line:84%
How far in advance is all
this stuff planned out?

00:16:55.870 --> 00:16:57.547 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: Wouldn't
it be nice to know?

00:16:57.547 --> 00:16:59.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, that was
all known before the war even

00:16:59.880 --> 00:17:00.510 align:middle line:90%
started.

00:17:00.510 --> 00:17:02.093 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: But there
was collaboration

00:17:02.093 --> 00:17:06.210 align:middle line:84%
between the United States,
and industry, and the Nazis.

00:17:06.210 --> 00:17:07.849 align:middle line:84%
The Bank for
International settlement

00:17:07.849 --> 00:17:13.180 align:middle line:84%
was almost in the
pockets of the Nazis.

00:17:13.180 --> 00:17:15.109 align:middle line:84%
And it has a very
bad reputation,

00:17:15.109 --> 00:17:21.619 align:middle line:84%
and was supposed to have
been wound up after the war.

00:17:21.619 --> 00:17:23.730 align:middle line:84%
But it had some
friends in court,

00:17:23.730 --> 00:17:27.270 align:middle line:84%
and one way or another,
managed to escape.

00:17:27.270 --> 00:17:32.670 align:middle line:84%
And then it has become
sort of the regulator--

00:17:32.670 --> 00:17:36.050 align:middle line:84%
it is a regulator--
of the banking system.

00:17:36.050 --> 00:17:39.360 align:middle line:84%
And they're the ones
that set the rules that

00:17:39.360 --> 00:17:45.265 align:middle line:84%
say that the banks can use
$0.05 to create a dollar.

00:17:45.265 --> 00:17:46.065 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:48.330 align:middle line:84%
And I just think it's
really important for people

00:17:48.330 --> 00:17:50.830 align:middle line:84%
to grokk the fact
that all of this

00:17:50.830 --> 00:17:55.460 align:middle line:84%
is happening behind
the scenes to engineer

00:17:55.460 --> 00:17:58.100 align:middle line:84%
certain people to rise
to power-- like Hitler,

00:17:58.100 --> 00:18:01.150 align:middle line:84%
for example--
certain end scenarios

00:18:01.150 --> 00:18:05.750 align:middle line:84%
so that certain other
companies and corporations

00:18:05.750 --> 00:18:07.970 align:middle line:84%
within the
military-industrial complex

00:18:07.970 --> 00:18:11.220 align:middle line:84%
will continue prospering through
the whole process and beyond,

00:18:11.220 --> 00:18:14.000 align:middle line:84%
to say nothing of the banking
industry, the Warburgs,

00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:16.900 align:middle line:84%
for example, being really
central to that theme.

00:18:16.900 --> 00:18:19.230 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you ever--
I mean, it's controversial,

00:18:19.230 --> 00:18:21.660 align:middle line:84%
but there is a little
book that was written

00:18:21.660 --> 00:18:23.410 align:middle line:84%
called "The Secret
Backers of Hitler,"

00:18:23.410 --> 00:18:26.480 align:middle line:84%
for example, that was supposedly
an end-of-life confessional

00:18:26.480 --> 00:18:29.350 align:middle line:84%
by one of the Warburgs,
saying, he-- he spoke German.

00:18:29.350 --> 00:18:30.790 align:middle line:90%
He was from Germany.

00:18:30.790 --> 00:18:33.230 align:middle line:84%
And he was actually
doing the business

00:18:33.230 --> 00:18:35.810 align:middle line:84%
of running the checks
between the Wall Street

00:18:35.810 --> 00:18:38.870 align:middle line:84%
bankers and Hitler, to help
get him up and running.

00:18:38.870 --> 00:18:41.270 align:middle line:84%
Many of the families-- who
were Jewish, by the way.

00:18:41.270 --> 00:18:43.320 align:middle line:84%
So there was this
whole thing where

00:18:43.320 --> 00:18:46.630 align:middle line:84%
money transcends all of
these other lines and issues.

00:18:46.630 --> 00:18:50.830 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter who suffers
at the end in the name of money.

00:18:50.830 --> 00:18:52.060 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:18:52.060 --> 00:19:00.630 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: It's an
insidious and evil system.

00:19:00.630 --> 00:19:01.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:19:01.430 --> 00:19:03.470 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: I don't
often use that word.

00:19:03.470 --> 00:19:10.180 align:middle line:84%
My wife insists that I say that
the people responsible for it,

00:19:10.180 --> 00:19:13.837 align:middle line:84%
there are evil consequences
of their actions.

00:19:13.837 --> 00:19:15.670 align:middle line:84%
So let's give them the
benefit of the doubt.

00:19:15.670 --> 00:19:17.720 align:middle line:90%
We can't get inside their minds.

00:19:17.720 --> 00:19:20.740 align:middle line:84%
But the system is
evil because it

00:19:20.740 --> 00:19:27.980 align:middle line:84%
is making debt slaves of just
about everybody in the world.

00:19:27.980 --> 00:19:33.750 align:middle line:84%
And it's creating a class of
very, very, very rich people.

00:19:33.750 --> 00:19:37.680 align:middle line:84%
You read about it in the
papers periodically now,

00:19:37.680 --> 00:19:40.510 align:middle line:90%
the pyramid of wealth.

00:19:40.510 --> 00:19:44.050 align:middle line:84%
When you get to the very top,
people with so much money,

00:19:44.050 --> 00:19:46.860 align:middle line:84%
they don't even
put in the figures.

00:19:46.860 --> 00:19:49.630 align:middle line:84%
And then you've got
the multi-billionaires.

00:19:49.630 --> 00:19:51.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The
widening base of us.

00:19:51.290 --> 00:19:53.623 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: And then you get
the multi-multimillionaires,

00:19:53.623 --> 00:19:54.490 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:19:54.490 --> 00:19:56.330 align:middle line:90%
And then you get down.

00:19:56.330 --> 00:20:00.480 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's
1% of the people

00:20:00.480 --> 00:20:04.325 align:middle line:84%
are going to have
more money than all

00:20:04.325 --> 00:20:09.504 align:middle line:84%
of the people of the rest
of the world put together.

00:20:09.504 --> 00:20:13.260 align:middle line:90%
And that's not good.

00:20:13.260 --> 00:20:16.480 align:middle line:84%
And you know, one of the
things-- when globalization

00:20:16.480 --> 00:20:22.090 align:middle line:84%
came along, they
admitted that it

00:20:22.090 --> 00:20:26.790 align:middle line:84%
was going to have some
problems of redistribution.

00:20:26.790 --> 00:20:30.477 align:middle line:84%
But no one said what
the cure might be.

00:20:30.477 --> 00:20:32.060 align:middle line:84%
They kept writing,
saying, well, there

00:20:32.060 --> 00:20:34.530 align:middle line:84%
are some problems
we have to work out

00:20:34.530 --> 00:20:36.450 align:middle line:84%
about the redistribution
of wealth.

00:20:36.450 --> 00:20:40.470 align:middle line:84%
And maybe there's too much
money flowing to certain people.

00:20:40.470 --> 00:20:42.700 align:middle line:84%
But I never read an
article that said,

00:20:42.700 --> 00:20:45.475 align:middle line:90%
and the cure to this problem is.

00:20:45.475 --> 00:20:46.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You're right.

00:20:46.590 --> 00:20:46.940 align:middle line:90%
You're right.

00:20:46.940 --> 00:20:47.981 align:middle line:90%
You don't see that story.

00:20:47.981 --> 00:20:49.930 align:middle line:84%
Now, this brings us
to another topic,

00:20:49.930 --> 00:20:56.220 align:middle line:84%
which ameliorates a lot
of the effects of poverty,

00:20:56.220 --> 00:20:58.290 align:middle line:84%
for example, around the
world on many levels.

00:20:58.290 --> 00:21:01.110 align:middle line:84%
And that has to do with
our energy sources.

00:21:01.110 --> 00:21:04.110 align:middle line:84%
And as you've said in your book,
the banking industry, number

00:21:04.110 --> 00:21:07.930 align:middle line:84%
one at the top of
this very sick system.

00:21:07.930 --> 00:21:09.200 align:middle line:90%
Next under that is oil.

00:21:09.200 --> 00:21:10.000 align:middle line:90%
>>HELLYER: Mm-hmm.

00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:12.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And breaking
the oil cartels,

00:21:12.400 --> 00:21:15.510 align:middle line:84%
when I know for at
least the last 15 years

00:21:15.510 --> 00:21:18.770 align:middle line:84%
that I've been doing
this, you read about.

00:21:18.770 --> 00:21:22.190 align:middle line:84%
You run into an inventor
here and there saying,

00:21:22.190 --> 00:21:25.342 align:middle line:84%
I've got this little prototype,
and well on their way.

00:21:25.342 --> 00:21:26.800 align:middle line:84%
And if we look at
what happened out

00:21:26.800 --> 00:21:29.170 align:middle line:84%
of Roswell, from our
last conversation,

00:21:29.170 --> 00:21:32.990 align:middle line:84%
we're absolutely on our way to
being able to eliminate the oil

00:21:32.990 --> 00:21:34.070 align:middle line:90%
industry.

00:21:34.070 --> 00:21:35.160 align:middle line:90%
And let's talk about it.

00:21:35.160 --> 00:21:35.960 align:middle line:90%
Because--

00:21:35.960 --> 00:21:42.332 align:middle line:84%
>>HELLYER: In my book, I
say, our house is on fire.

00:21:42.332 --> 00:21:45.930 align:middle line:84%
